>> bench/domains/travel/classifier-labels.mld
>>
>> Hand-labeled travel user-task queries for classifier accuracy testing.
>>
>> Labels classify the user's task INTENT — what tool families the task
>> needs and whether the user is asking for a recommendation/ranking
>> (advice). Labels are derived from the prompt text alone, NOT from the
>> AgentDojo benchmark ground-truth tool sequences or evaluator output.
>>
>> `prompt` is the verbatim user query as it reaches the agent. Extracted
>> 2026-05-05 from agentdojo v1/v1_1_1 user_tasks.py PROMPT fields via
>> AST parse (no checker code touched).
>>
>> `tool_groups` is the set of domain families the task needs, drawn from
>> the keys of @toolSets in tools.mld: hotel, restaurant, car, flight,
>> calendar, email, user.
>>
>> `is_advice` is true when the user asks the agent to recommend, rank,
>> select-best-of, or filter-and-pick a candidate from multiple options
>> based on subjective or objective criteria. False when the user names
>> a specific entity and asks the agent to verify or look up information
>> about it. UT0 and UT1 are the only non-advice tasks: both name a hotel
>> ("Le Marais Boutique", "City Hub") and ask for conditional verification.
>>
>> `advice_kind` is informational. Single-domain tasks use the domain
>> name; multi-domain advice tasks use null.

>> Wrapped in an exe so primitive values materialize across module
>> imports — c-9c53 leaks Literal AST nodes through `var` exports of
>> records. exe returns force evaluation. Consumers call
>> @travelClassifierLabels() to read.
